## DeepSeek V4 Flash Free prompt splitter

If this prompt is too large for the active model, use one of these smaller prompts instead.

### Pass 35.0 · Repo sync and safety scan

```text
Execute only Phase 35.0 for cvsz/zdash. Inspect git status, Makefile, .gitignore, .codex/config.toml, and docs/prompt. Ensure docs/prompts/codex-runs/ is untracked and ignored. Do not change app code. Run make safety-scan. Fix only safety-scan false positives or tracked local-only files. Report exact commands and results.
```

### Pass 35.1 · Backend release hardening

```text
Execute only Phase 35.1 backend release hardening for cvsz/zdash. Inspect backend/app/main.py, backend/app/core/config.py, backend/app/api, backend/app/trading, backend/app/ai_trader, backend/app/risk, backend/app/content, backend/app/billing, backend/app/marketplace, backend/app/enterprise, and backend tests. Fix duplicate router registration, stale imports, response envelope inconsistencies, missing RBAC on sensitive routes, and obvious test failures only. Do not enable live trading or external broker execution. Run python -m ruff check app tests and python -B -m pytest -q with development env overrides.
```

### Pass 35.2 · AI Trader final polish

```text
Execute only Phase 35.2 AI Trader final polish for cvsz/zdash. Inspect backend/app/ai_trader, backend/app/api/ai_trader.py, backend/tests/test_ai_trader*, frontend/src/api/aiTrader.ts, frontend/src/components/trading/AITraderSimulationCard.tsx, and relevant frontend tests. Ensure AI Trader remains simulation-only, paper-trade forces dry_run=true, status reports live_execution_allowed=false, all metadata includes simulation_only=true, and no live trading button exists. Run targeted backend and frontend tests, then report.
```

### Pass 35.3 · Frontend dashboard/UI polish

```text
Execute only Phase 35.3 frontend dashboard/UI polish for cvsz/zdash. Inspect frontend/src/App.tsx, frontend/src/pages, frontend/src/components, frontend/src/api, and frontend/src/tests. Fix broken imports, route render failures, missing empty/loading/error states, unclear dry-run labels, duplicate UI code, and responsive issues. Do not change backend contracts unless required by failing tests. Run npm test and npm run build.
```

### Pass 35.4 · Docs/runbooks/API examples

```text
Execute only Phase 35.4 docs and runbooks for cvsz/zdash. Update README and docs only. API examples must use port 8005. Document Phase 35 release status, AI Trader simulation-only behavior, production safety notes, validation commands, common non-blocking warnings, and Cloudflare operator handoff to cvsz/zeaz-platform. Do not edit source code. Run make safety-scan.
```

### Pass 35.5 · Makefile/CI/maintenance validation

```text
Execute only Phase 35.5 Makefile, CI, and maintenance validation for cvsz/zdash. Inspect Makefile, .github/workflows, .codex/cloud/maintenance.sh, .gitignore, and env examples. Ensure scans check tracked runtime/source files only and do not fail on ignored caches. Keep .env and local Codex run artifacts untracked. Run make safety-scan, make validate-fast, and if Docker is available make validate.
```

### Pass 35.6 · Final report and release handoff

```text
Execute only Phase 35.6 final report for cvsz/zdash. Do not edit files unless validation reveals a critical small issue. Summarize repository inspection, files changed across Phase 35, validation results, safety checklist, AI Trader status, billing/mock/Stripe status, marketplace safety, enterprise export safety, Cloudflare operator handoff, known warnings, known limitations, and next phase recommendation.
```

---

## Non-negotiable safety invariants

- Do not enable live trading.
- Do not add real broker order execution.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass `TradingService`, `ExecutionEngine`, `SignalValidationService`, RBAC, audit/event logging, dry-run mode, or existing zDash safety policy.
- AI Trader remains simulation-only / paper-trading only.
- Content publishing remains approval-gated and dry-run by default.
- Billing provider remains mock by default.
- Stripe remains disabled by default unless explicitly configured outside this phase.
- Marketplace plugin runtime remains sandboxed by default.
- Marketplace review is required by default.
- Enterprise license must never disable `PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK`.
- No raw secrets, `.env`, GPG passphrases, token dumps, private keys, payment secrets, API keys, or Cloudflare tokens may be committed.
- `docs/prompts/codex-runs/` must remain local-only and untracked.
- Backend port is `8005`; do not introduce `localhost:8000` or `BACKEND_PORT=8000` outside archived/local-only prompt artifacts.
- All risky flows must show visible safety copy in UI.
- All financial/trading UI must include simulation-only / not financial advice language.

