## Scope A · Backend finalization

Complete backend release readiness:

- Verify every router is registered once in `backend/app/main.py`.
- Verify every API response follows the existing response envelope style.
- Verify auth/RBAC on all sensitive endpoints.
- Verify tenancy isolation on billing, marketplace, enterprise, trading, AI trader, content, and collaboration data.
- Verify dry-run defaults and production safety lock behavior.
- Verify `APP_ENV=production` requires PostgreSQL and secure settings.
- Verify SQLite remains allowed only in development/test.
- Verify backend health, metrics, admin, audit, realtime, scheduler, trading, AI trader, content, billing, marketplace, and enterprise routes work.
- Remove dead imports, duplicate route registration, stale TODO-only code, and unreachable logic.
- Do not remove working phase modules.

Expected backend checks:

```bash
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
APP_ENV=development \
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./zdash_test.db \
PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true \
DRY_RUN=true \
LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false \
python -m ruff check app tests
APP_ENV=development \
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./zdash_test.db \
PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true \
DRY_RUN=true \
LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false \
python -B -m pytest -q
```

---

## Scope B · Frontend finalization

Complete frontend release readiness:

- Verify all sidebar/topbar routes render.
- Verify dashboard cards show safe fallback states.
- Verify XAU/Trading page shows dry-run, Guardian, and simulation disclaimers.
- Verify AI Trader panel shows strategy selection, compare, validation, dry-run-only execution, and no live-trading button.
- Verify billing pages show mock billing banner when provider is mock.
- Verify marketplace pages show plugin safety and review requirements.
- Verify enterprise pages sanitize/escape branding fields and require confirmation for secret export.
- Verify onboarding encourages dry-run validation before production.
- Verify settings page does not expose secrets.
- Verify responsive layout and empty/loading/error states.
- Remove duplicate imports, stale unreachable code, and broken UI labels.

Expected frontend checks:

```bash
cd frontend
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh
nvm use 20
npm test
npm run build
```

---

## Scope C · AI Trader final release polish

Finalize the AI Trader Simulation Control Plane:

- Ensure status endpoint reports `simulation_only=true`, `dry_run_forced=true`, and `live_execution_allowed=false`.
- Ensure strategies endpoint lists all deterministic strategies.
- Ensure signal endpoint returns signal, validation, features, warnings, explanation, risk policy, and safety notice.
- Ensure compare endpoint returns ranked strategy decisions without enabling execution.
- Ensure paper-trade endpoint forces dry-run through existing execution engine.
- Ensure every signal metadata includes `simulation_only=true` and `risk_policy.live_execution_allowed=false`.
- Ensure no external ML dependency is added.
- Ensure tests cover insufficient candles, malformed candles, buy/sell/hold, comparison, and dry-run paper-trade.

---

## Scope D · Dashboard and UI/UX release polish

Improve UI/UX without large redesign churn:

- Standardize card titles, badges, safety banners, empty states, and loading states.
- Keep a consistent dark dashboard visual style.
- Ensure all action buttons communicate dry-run/simulation status.
- Ensure dangerous actions require confirmation and reason where applicable.
- Improve dashboard information hierarchy.
- Add missing tests for critical UI paths only.
- Do not add unnecessary dependencies.

