## Commit

Use one final commit if changes are small and cohesive:

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "phase35: finalize zdash release candidate"
```

If many unrelated fixes are required, split commits by area:

```bash
git commit -m "phase35: harden backend release checks"
git commit -m "phase35: polish frontend release dashboard"
git commit -m "phase35: update final release documentation"
```

For DeepSeek V4 Flash Free pass-split execution, use pass-specific commits:

```bash
git commit -m "phase35.1: harden backend release checks"
git commit -m "phase35.2: finalize ai trader simulation polish"
git commit -m "phase35.3: polish frontend dashboard release ui"
git commit -m "phase35.4: update release documentation"
git commit -m "phase35.5: harden validation and maintenance checks"
```
